criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with chronic heart failure (CHF), classified in NYHA functional class III or
             IV;

          -  Receiving optimal medical therapy for CHF (including an angiotensin-converting enzyme
             inhibitor or an angiotensin receptor blocker and a beta-blocker unless a
             contraindication is evident) with a stable condition for more than 1 month (no
             hospitalization for HF, no change in medication, and no change in NYHA functional
             class);

          -  Left ventricular ejection fraction (LVEF) < 35%;

          -  QRS duration ≥ 120 ms.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  If they are younger than 18 years or are unable to sign informed consent;

          -  Patients who had been treated with an intravenous inotropic agent within the 30 days
             prior to implantation (these medications affect endothelial function after they are
             discontinued);

          -  Unstable angina pectoris;

          -  Orthopedic or neurological limitations to exercise.
